23:37.450 --> 23:38.082
Miss.

23:38.084 --> 23:40.151
I'm not married.

23:40.153 --> 23:42.019
Months ago.

23:42.021 --> 23:43.053
July, maybe.

23:43.055 --> 23:45.756
My cycles are very irregular.

23:45.758 --> 23:48.426
Well, seems you're
about 12 weeks pregnant.

23:51.898 --> 23:52.696
What?

23:59.005 --> 24:00.638
That's impossible.

24:00.640 --> 24:03.073
No, it isn't.

24:03.075 --> 24:05.543
You're three months pregnant.

24:05.545 --> 24:06.610
Nature works miracles.

24:10.616 --> 24:13.951
Have you had any recreational
drugs during this period?

24:18.124 --> 24:21.959
I-- I can't be.

24:21.961 --> 24:23.227
I have acute fibroids.

24:26.699 --> 24:28.799
The doctors say i
can never have a baby

24:28.801 --> 24:31.635
or get pregnant, unless
i went through invitro.

24:31.637 --> 24:34.839
Well, it looks like
they were wrong.

24:34.841 --> 24:35.906
Congratulations.

24:35.908 --> 24:36.874
No.

24:36.876 --> 24:39.910
No, you don't understand.

24:39.912 --> 24:41.078
I cannot have this baby.

24:41.080 --> 24:43.481
I'm not married.

24:43.483 --> 24:48.519
The father is-- it's
just not the right time.

24:51.224 --> 24:54.825
Blake's gonna kill
me when he finds out.

24:54.827 --> 24:57.228
You take it easy.

24:57.230 --> 25:00.030
We'll forward the results of
your test to your physician.

25:00.032 --> 25:01.765
You follow through with him.

25:01.767 --> 25:06.070
Miss louann will give you
some prenatal vitamins.

25:20.219 --> 25:22.686
Take your time.

28:43.756 --> 28:44.455
Emergency.

28:44.457 --> 28:45.222
What is your location?

28:45.224 --> 28:46.090
Location?

28:46.092 --> 28:46.924
I don't know.

28:46.926 --> 28:47.858
Wyoming county.

28:47.860 --> 28:48.859
It's an emergency.

28:48.861 --> 28:50.427
My name is Angelica santoro.

28:50.429 --> 28:53.163
Hello?

28:53.165 --> 28:53.964
Shit.

29:54.093 --> 29:55.993
Hey, babe, it's me.

29:55.995 --> 29:59.029
I'm worried.

29:59.031 --> 30:00.531
You were on your way
home about an hour ago.

30:04.236 --> 30:05.035
Call me.

30:15.314 --> 30:17.915
Your call
cannot be completed as dialed.

30:17.917 --> 30:18.882
Please check--

33:35.447 --> 33:37.014
who the hell is that?

33:42.721 --> 33:43.687
Get the dogs.

33:48.427 --> 33:49.393
Come on!

34:08.781 --> 34:11.380
Ah!

34:36.708 --> 34:39.543
911, can I help you?

34:39.545 --> 34:40.510
Hello.

34:40.512 --> 34:42.179
My name is Blake blackman.

34:42.181 --> 34:43.780
I'd like to report the
disappearance of my girlfriend.

34:49.588 --> 34:53.156
This is your
fault. She followed you!

34:53.158 --> 34:54.157
Did you go into town?

34:54.159 --> 34:55.559
Well, I told you not to!

34:55.561 --> 34:56.525
Are you demented woman?

34:56.527 --> 34:58.528
I had a flat tire!

35:05.838 --> 35:07.437
They don't be looking for him.

35:07.439 --> 35:09.406
They don't be looking for him.

35:09.408 --> 35:10.440
I have.

35:10.442 --> 35:11.241
Shh.

35:13.679 --> 35:14.578
Who are you?

35:14.580 --> 35:15.378
Who's there?

35:18.317 --> 35:19.116
Us.

35:22.621 --> 35:23.553
Who's us?

35:27.259 --> 35:29.559
When was the last
time you saw her, sir?

35:29.561 --> 35:31.361
About 9 o'clock this morning.

35:31.363 --> 35:34.664
She went into town to get some
groceries and to see a doctor.

35:34.666 --> 35:35.765
What doctor?

35:35.767 --> 35:39.136
She wasn't feeling well.

35:39.138 --> 35:39.903
You got any pictures of her?

35:39.905 --> 35:40.904
No.

35:40.906 --> 35:42.873
No pictures.

35:42.875 --> 35:45.475
Not even on your cell?

35:45.477 --> 35:46.543
No.

35:46.545 --> 35:48.411
Did she contact
you at all, sir?

35:48.413 --> 35:50.881
Yeah, actually, she
texted me around noon

35:50.883 --> 35:53.150
and told me that
she was coming back.

35:53.152 --> 35:54.384
May I see some ID, please.

36:02.261 --> 36:04.594
New York.

36:04.596 --> 36:05.695
We don't get
tourists around here.

36:05.697 --> 36:07.197
We're not.

36:07.199 --> 36:09.232
I'm a writer and she's
a book illustrator.

36:09.234 --> 36:10.734
My editor in new
York owns the cabin.

36:10.736 --> 36:13.737
His name is sherman Rogers,
and I'm using his place

36:13.739 --> 36:15.172
to work on my next novel.

36:15.174 --> 36:16.439
What do you write?

36:16.441 --> 36:17.374
Horror novels.

36:21.246 --> 36:24.447
You mind if we
take a look around?

36:24.449 --> 36:27.284
Yeah, sure.

36:42.267 --> 36:44.234
Hey, Steve.

36:44.236 --> 36:45.569
Take a look at this.

36:55.280 --> 36:56.346
This guy's hiding something.

37:04.489 --> 37:05.522
Mr. blackman?

37:05.524 --> 37:07.490
Did you send for other units?

37:07.492 --> 37:09.526
I'm gonna have to ask
you to come to the station

37:09.528 --> 37:10.961
with us, mr blackman.
-The station?

37:10.963 --> 37:12.429
What are you kidding me?

37:12.431 --> 37:13.563
Why aren't you out
there looking for her?

37:13.565 --> 37:15.332
Sir, we understand
you're upset,

37:15.334 --> 37:16.666
but you're going to have to
file a missing persons report.

37:23.375 --> 37:24.674
Well, come on, then.
Let's go.

37:24.676 --> 37:25.875
How much more time
you gonna waste?

37:30.549 --> 37:32.582
Nancy, what are you
still doing here?

37:39.658 --> 37:40.657
Sir.

37:40.659 --> 37:42.359
I'm already home, Thompson.

37:42.361 --> 37:42.959
We've got a situation.

38:00.746 --> 38:01.711
Finally.

38:01.713 --> 38:02.612
What the hell's going on?

38:02.614 --> 38:03.880
Sir, please take a seat.

38:03.882 --> 38:05.815
I've been sitting on
my ass long enough.

38:05.817 --> 38:06.916
Why are you wasting time?

38:06.918 --> 38:09.019
Calm down, Mr. blackman.

38:09.021 --> 38:10.887
I'm sheriff McFadden.

38:10.889 --> 38:13.923
I think we need to talk.

38:13.925 --> 38:15.425
Ok, sheriff.

38:15.427 --> 38:17.394
Let's talk.

38:17.396 --> 38:19.562
Why aren't you out there
searching for my girlfriend?

38:19.564 --> 38:21.031
I already told you
everything I know.

38:21.033 --> 38:22.432
Hey!

38:22.434 --> 38:23.066
Take it easy.

38:23.068 --> 38:24.501
It's ok, Thompson.

38:24.503 --> 38:25.969
No, you didn't.

38:25.971 --> 38:28.938
Your background check came back.

38:28.940 --> 38:32.842
You're a married man, Mr.
blackman, to Claire borts.

38:32.844 --> 38:34.477
What difference does that make?

38:34.479 --> 38:35.512
You liked to the police.

38:35.514 --> 38:37.380
I didn't lie.

38:37.382 --> 38:40.450
I just-- yes, I'll
married and I'm

38:40.452 --> 38:41.451
having an affair with Angie.

38:41.453 --> 38:43.386
But that's private.

38:43.388 --> 38:44.821
What really matters
is you guys going

38:44.823 --> 38:46.723
out there and finding her.

38:46.725 --> 38:51.594
See, telling the truth
wasn't that hard, now, was it?

38:51.596 --> 38:53.730
Why don't we start all over?

38:53.732 --> 38:55.365
And this time you
tell us everything.

38:58.670 --> 39:02.505
Angelica santoro.

39:02.507 --> 39:09.346
Mmm, 35-- 35 years old.

39:09.648 --> 39:12.549
Florida driver's license.

39:12.551 --> 39:15.719
We met a year ago at one of
my book signings in New York.

39:15.721 --> 39:17.754
She's an illustrator.

39:17.756 --> 39:20.023
And my editor, sherman
Rogers introduced us.

39:20.025 --> 39:21.891
What are you doing down here?

39:21.893 --> 39:23.393
I'm working on my next novel.

39:23.395 --> 39:25.061
Anybody know you're
here together?

39:25.063 --> 39:26.996
Nobody knows.

39:26.998 --> 39:28.598
What about her family.

39:28.600 --> 39:30.033
Her mother lives
in Miami and thinks

39:30.035 --> 39:32.469
she's in Chicago for work.

39:32.471 --> 39:33.670
Anything else?

39:36.508 --> 39:39.843
Mr. blackman,
answer the question.

39:45.550 --> 39:49.619
When we arrived, she
was playing with the dog

39:49.621 --> 39:52.489
and she swore somebody
was out there.

39:52.491 --> 39:53.123
Where?

39:53.125 --> 39:54.891
In the woods.

39:54.893 --> 39:58.928
And we even argued about it
because I didn't believe her.

39:58.930 --> 40:01.498
Did it become physical at all?

40:04.803 --> 40:07.137
No.

40:07.139 --> 40:09.539
What are we gonna do?

40:09.541 --> 40:11.040
We gonna get rid of her.

40:11.042 --> 40:12.575
Let me go!

40:12.577 --> 40:14.110
Send all units first
thing in the morning

40:14.112 --> 40:15.545
and search the entire county.

40:15.547 --> 40:16.579
Are you kidding me?

40:16.581 --> 40:18.782
Why not tonight?

40:18.784 --> 40:20.950
The officers will
take you back.

40:20.952 --> 40:23.186
If she hadn't
appeared by morning,

40:23.188 --> 40:24.821
we're going to have
to notify the family.

40:24.823 --> 40:29.159
Sheriff, tomorrow
maybe too late.

40:29.161 --> 40:29.959
Thompson.

40:37.903 --> 40:38.701
Angie!

40:41.039 --> 40:41.838
Angie!

40:44.776 --> 40:45.575
Angie!

40:48.146 --> 40:48.978
Angie!

40:52.017 --> 40:54.584
Angie!

41:02.594 --> 41:04.093
Blake?

41:04.095 --> 41:05.094
Blake?

41:05.096 --> 41:06.663
Sherman, we've got to talk.

41:06.665 --> 41:09.466
Remember Angelica,
Angelica santoro?

41:09.468 --> 41:10.200
The book illustrator?

41:10.202 --> 41:11.234
Yeah.

41:11.236 --> 41:12.836
We've been seeing each other.

41:12.838 --> 41:14.671
But I thought you said
there was nothing to that.

41:14.673 --> 41:16.039
I lied.

41:16.041 --> 41:17.874
We've been having an
affair for the past year.

41:17.876 --> 41:21.244
I brought her up here
with me to the cabin.

41:21.246 --> 41:22.779
Now she's gone.

41:22.781 --> 41:23.780
She's missing.

41:23.782 --> 41:24.914
What do you mean by missing?

41:24.916 --> 41:25.849
Come on, sherman.

41:25.851 --> 41:27.684
She's missing!

41:27.686 --> 41:29.619
She went out this
morning to town.

41:29.621 --> 41:30.987
She never came back.

41:30.989 --> 41:32.222
I called the police.

41:32.224 --> 41:33.857
They're searching for her now.

41:33.859 --> 41:36.726
I filed a missing
persons report.

41:36.728 --> 41:40.029
Sherman, if anything
happens to her--

41:40.031 --> 41:41.498
well, wait a second.

41:41.500 --> 41:43.066
You're telling me
that you took this girl

41:43.068 --> 41:44.934
with you up to West Virginia.

41:44.936 --> 41:46.703
And now something may
have happened to her?

41:46.705 --> 41:48.271
-And there's something else.
-What?

41:48.273 --> 41:50.173
They think I may have
done something to her.

41:50.175 --> 41:51.941
Like foul play?

41:51.943 --> 41:53.710
This isn't good.

41:53.712 --> 41:56.813
You're gonna need an attorney.

41:56.815 --> 41:57.647
Don't go anywhere.

41:57.649 --> 41:58.615
I'll call you back.

42:48.333 --> 42:49.132
Angie!

42:53.305 --> 42:54.103
Angie!

43:01.279 --> 43:02.078
Angie!

43:48.360 --> 43:50.727
You best be telling
the truth now, you hear!

43:50.729 --> 43:52.662
I swear no one else is here!

43:52.664 --> 43:53.296
No one else.

43:53.298 --> 43:54.197
No.

43:54.199 --> 43:55.231
I swear, it was just me.

43:55.233 --> 43:56.065
I swear.

43:56.067 --> 43:56.899
Let me go.

43:56.901 --> 43:58.067
Please let me go.

43:58.069 --> 44:00.036
Well, dang, what
are we gonna do?

44:00.038 --> 44:02.238
We gonna kill her.

44:02.240 --> 44:03.106
No!

44:03.108 --> 44:04.641
Please!

44:04.643 --> 44:05.942
I'm p-- I'm pregnant.

44:05.944 --> 44:07.010
Have mercy, please.

44:07.012 --> 44:09.312
Ah!

44:09.314 --> 44:11.180
You think
we stupid people?

44:11.182 --> 44:12.749
You think we dumb, huh?

44:12.751 --> 44:14.283
Is that what you think?

44:14.285 --> 44:16.819
My purse.

44:16.821 --> 44:17.787
Look in my purse.

44:17.789 --> 44:21.124
In my purse..

44:29.668 --> 44:30.700
So what!

44:30.702 --> 44:32.001
We still gotta get rid of her!

44:32.003 --> 44:32.835
But wait.

44:32.837 --> 44:33.670
Wait!

44:33.672 --> 44:34.837
I've got me an idea.

44:34.839 --> 44:35.672
No, Margaret.

44:35.674 --> 44:36.339
No more ideas!

44:36.341 --> 44:38.107
No ideas!

44:38.109 --> 44:41.377
But we could keep her a couple
months till the baby's born,

44:41.379 --> 44:43.780
and get rid of her.

44:43.782 --> 44:45.081
No!

44:45.083 --> 44:47.450
But what if it's
a boy, Leonard.

44:47.452 --> 44:50.319
We could keep him
and get rid of her.

44:50.321 --> 44:52.321
They gonna be lookin' for her.

44:52.323 --> 44:55.224
We ain't gonna do nothin'
of the kind, Margaret.

44:55.226 --> 44:57.160
Leonard cunnings!

44:57.162 --> 44:59.729
You knows what I always wanted.

45:03.702 --> 45:04.867
You got two boys already!

45:04.869 --> 45:06.936
What you want another one for?

45:06.938 --> 45:08.204
No, we ain't gonna
discuss this now!

45:08.206 --> 45:09.005
We ain't!

45:12.711 --> 45:13.409
Mr. Rogers.

45:13.411 --> 45:14.310
What!

45:14.312 --> 45:16.245
Mr. Rogers!

45:16.247 --> 45:17.080
What is it?

45:19.784 --> 45:21.317
I've got Claire
blackman on the phone.

45:21.319 --> 45:23.286
She says it's urgent.

45:23.288 --> 45:25.054
Put her on the phone and
close the door behind you.

45:25.056 --> 45:26.122
Yes, sir.

45:26.124 --> 45:28.224
Where the hell's
my.

45:28.226 --> 45:29.726
Get me Kaufman on the phone.

45:29.728 --> 45:30.893
Tell him it's urgent.
It can't wait.

45:30.895 --> 45:31.494
Ok.

45:37.836 --> 45:39.869
Claire?

45:39.871 --> 45:40.503
I know.

45:40.505 --> 45:41.804
I spoke with him.

45:41.806 --> 45:43.206
It's bad.

45:43.208 --> 45:45.775
He went up there with
someone, Claire-- a woman.

45:48.947 --> 45:50.279
Yes, her.

45:50.281 --> 45:52.448
The girl went missing,
and they can't find her.

45:52.450 --> 45:54.183
He had to file a
missing persons report.

46:04.362 --> 46:05.361
Ow.

46:05.363 --> 46:06.195
I know it hurts.

46:06.197 --> 46:07.029
Hold on.

46:08.533 --> 46:13.770
It's gonna make you feel a
lot better-- so much better.

46:13.772 --> 46:14.771
Trust me.

46:21.212 --> 46:23.146
Put your arm in that one.

46:31.022 --> 46:31.854
There we go.

46:37.028 --> 46:39.962
Where are ya?

46:39.964 --> 46:42.365
Where's your-- yeah.

46:42.367 --> 46:43.933
I got your mouth right there.

46:43.935 --> 46:45.468
Come on.

46:45.470 --> 46:46.269
Uh-uh!

46:49.240 --> 46:51.440
Don't be a damn fool!

46:51.442 --> 46:54.210
You want your baby
to live, don't ya?

46:57.448 --> 46:59.015
Can I have some?

46:59.017 --> 47:02.051
Shut up!

47:02.053 --> 47:05.822
If you want to eat
today, best be quiet!

47:05.824 --> 47:06.489
Come on.

47:06.491 --> 47:07.590
Uh-uh!

47:07.592 --> 47:09.058
Well, suit yourself!

47:11.496 --> 47:13.529
Let me take this thing off.

47:20.004 --> 47:23.005
Look at me.

47:23.007 --> 47:25.441
Look at me.

47:25.443 --> 47:26.242
Oh.

47:29.180 --> 47:31.047
You are so purty.

47:34.519 --> 47:38.855
Oh, you're going to give
me a beautiful baby!

47:38.857 --> 47:41.390
Oh!

47:41.392 --> 47:42.191
Oh!

47:47.565 --> 47:50.199
And I don't want to hear
a peep out of anybody!

48:03.481 --> 48:05.081
Don't cry.

48:05.083 --> 48:06.282
They don't like us crying.

48:10.288 --> 48:12.121
What's your name?

48:12.123 --> 48:13.389
Emmett.

48:13.391 --> 48:14.924
He's Jamie.

48:14.926 --> 48:16.626
Shut up, Emmett.

48:16.628 --> 48:18.194
Why?

48:18.196 --> 48:20.329
I'm not gonna hurt
you, I promise.

48:20.331 --> 48:24.634
There was another boy, but
Leonard took him to the lagoon

48:24.636 --> 48:26.168
after he tried to escape.

48:26.170 --> 48:28.070
The lagoon?

48:28.072 --> 48:30.306
In the back of the property.

48:30.308 --> 48:32.041
He never came back.

48:32.043 --> 48:36.579
You mean-- oh my god.

48:36.581 --> 48:37.413
Oh my god.

48:37.415 --> 48:38.214
Oh my god.

48:53.164 --> 48:54.263
Sherman, I'm losing it.

48:54.265 --> 48:56.132
Blake, listen up.

48:56.134 --> 48:57.300
I'm here with Eric Kaufman.

48:57.302 --> 48:59.402
I want you to listen
very carefully.

48:59.404 --> 49:02.238
Write this name down.

49:02.240 --> 49:04.206
This is an old friend of
mine who lives down there.

49:04.208 --> 49:06.375
We used to go hunting together.

49:06.377 --> 49:09.145
He worked for the police
department many years ago.

49:09.147 --> 49:11.347
Are you ready?

49:11.349 --> 49:18.287
Melbourne 304-556-7889.

49:20.725 --> 49:21.657
And one more thing.

49:25.163 --> 49:26.329
Your wife called.

49:26.331 --> 49:27.163
Great.

49:27.165 --> 49:29.598
When?

49:29.600 --> 49:33.102
I kind of told her, Blake.

49:33.104 --> 49:34.203
I had to.

49:34.205 --> 49:35.004
What'd she say?

49:42.547 --> 49:44.113
Blake.

49:44.115 --> 49:46.282
It's Eric.

49:46.284 --> 49:48.184
You're not going to like this.

49:48.186 --> 49:50.753
Your wife, based on the
voicemail you left her,

49:50.755 --> 49:52.054
is testifying against you.

50:08.373 --> 50:14.110
Just what we're need in
castle rock-- another atrocity.

50:14.112 --> 50:16.512
How many months pregnant, Jack?

50:16.514 --> 50:17.747
Three.

50:17.749 --> 50:21.484
And she had no idea
she was pregnant?

50:21.486 --> 50:24.186
There's more.

50:24.188 --> 50:28.524
Um, well, when i
confirmed her diagnosis,

50:28.526 --> 50:31.360
she became very disturbed.

50:31.362 --> 50:32.628
What do you mean?

50:32.630 --> 50:35.097
She said that the
father of the child

50:35.099 --> 50:37.733
was gonna kill her
when he found out.

50:48.513 --> 50:50.479
Anything?

50:50.481 --> 50:52.048
I'm afraid we're
gonna have to ask

50:52.050 --> 50:54.517
for a DNA test, Mr. blackman.

50:54.519 --> 50:56.118
There's enough
evidence to consider

50:56.120 --> 50:57.186
you a person of interest.

50:57.188 --> 50:57.820
Evidence?

50:57.822 --> 50:59.155
What evidence?

50:59.157 --> 51:01.424
We have a statement
from your wife

51:01.426 --> 51:05.461
that says the day
miss santoro vanished,

51:05.463 --> 51:07.229
you left her a
message confessing

51:07.231 --> 51:09.799
that you had done something
you felt terribly guilty about.

51:09.801 --> 51:11.667
Is she out of her mind?

51:11.669 --> 51:14.103
Yes, I left her a message
because I wanted to tell

51:14.105 --> 51:16.205
her the truth about the affair!

51:16.207 --> 51:20.176
Miss santoro was three
months pregnant, Mr. blackman.

51:28.419 --> 51:30.753
No.

51:30.755 --> 51:31.754
Wait.

51:31.756 --> 51:35.291
That's not possible.

51:35.293 --> 51:38.727
She called 911 about
the time she should

51:38.729 --> 51:42.598
have arrived back at the cabin.

51:42.600 --> 51:43.399
What?

51:46.337 --> 51:48.637
911?

51:51.576 --> 51:54.810
Mr. blackman,
you're under arrest.

51:54.812 --> 51:57.346
You have the right
to remain silent.

51:57.348 --> 51:59.715
Everything you say could be used
against you in a court of law.

51:59.717 --> 52:02.118
You have the right
to an attorney,

52:02.120 --> 52:04.787
have him present with you
while being questioned.

52:08.326 --> 52:11.393
As you wish.

53:16.794 --> 53:18.661
She's pregnant, Eric.

53:18.663 --> 53:19.695
The symptoms were there.

53:19.697 --> 53:21.630
It just never crossed my mind.

53:21.632 --> 53:23.832
So far it's a
circumstantial case.

53:23.834 --> 53:25.801
They have no
evidence against you.

53:25.803 --> 53:27.536
They're going to let
you go for a while,

53:27.538 --> 53:29.605
but this will give us time
to build the defense for you.

53:29.607 --> 53:32.808
Your wife's statement about
the phone call you made to her,

53:32.810 --> 53:33.976
it's not helping.

53:33.978 --> 53:36.445
I mean this is--
this is crazy, Eric.

53:36.447 --> 53:37.846
I called her to set
things straight,

53:37.848 --> 53:39.648
to tell her about everything.

53:39.650 --> 53:40.983
Well, you're going to have to
stay in this area for a while

53:40.985 --> 53:43.219
until we get this
straightened out.

53:43.221 --> 53:44.486
I know.

53:44.488 --> 53:45.788
Are you sure you
want to do this?

53:49.560 --> 53:51.827
It's not a good idea.

53:51.829 --> 53:54.830
As your attorney, I'm
advising you against it.

53:54.832 --> 53:56.265
This could all play against you.

54:21.959 --> 54:23.025
Hey, girl.

54:32.937 --> 54:34.937
Come on over here.

54:34.939 --> 54:38.907
That-a girl.

54:38.909 --> 54:40.009
I miss her too.

55:13.678 --> 55:16.545
--The flood
damaged crops will cost more,

55:16.547 --> 55:20.716
and that rain will delay harvest
in the Southern part of the us.

55:20.718 --> 55:21.884
How long have
you known sherman?

55:21.886 --> 55:23.986
Long enough to do him a favor.

55:23.988 --> 55:27.990
Yeah, well, he says
you're a stand up guy.

55:27.992 --> 55:29.491
He exaggerates.

55:29.493 --> 55:31.527
You used to work for
the police department?

55:31.529 --> 55:32.861
Years ago.

55:32.863 --> 55:34.730
And
now to our next story.

55:34.732 --> 55:37.833
A New York horror writer by
the name of Blake blackman

55:37.835 --> 55:40.536
is the official suspect
in the disappearance

55:40.538 --> 55:43.706
of his lover, Angelica
santoro, a book

55:43.708 --> 55:47.042
illustrator who went missing
days ago in Wyoming county,

55:47.044 --> 55:48.377
West Virginia.

55:48.379 --> 55:49.978
Sources report the
married suspect

55:49.980 --> 55:53.515
agreed to take a polygraph
test, which he failed.

55:53.517 --> 55:55.651
This is the fourth
missing persons

55:55.653 --> 55:58.053
case in the castle rock area.

55:58.055 --> 56:00.723
Lie detector test, huh?

56:00.725 --> 56:02.124
Not a smart move.

56:02.126 --> 56:03.726
You may write about
sinister things,

56:03.728 --> 56:05.828
but it don't mean
you are sinister.

56:05.830 --> 56:08.530
People tend to confuse
fiction with reality.

56:08.532 --> 56:10.532
And that's what
you're up against.

56:10.534 --> 56:12.134
Finding a missing persons
is one of the hardest

56:12.136 --> 56:16.405
things, especially after
the first 48 hours.

56:16.407 --> 56:18.974
It could take a day.

56:18.976 --> 56:19.942
It could take a lifetime.

56:31.956 --> 56:34.857
Yes, he should be
here at any moment.

56:34.859 --> 56:36.558
I understand that.

56:36.560 --> 56:39.061
But it took us five months
to get him to come up here.

56:39.063 --> 56:44.133
I think the board should
reconsider its decision, sir.

56:44.135 --> 56:45.834
I understand.

56:45.836 --> 56:47.469
Yes, Kaufman is here.

56:47.471 --> 56:50.005
We have the paperwork ready.

56:50.007 --> 56:51.106
Ok?

56:51.108 --> 56:52.074
I'll call you when we're done.

56:54.945 --> 56:56.111
They're going ahead with it.

56:56.113 --> 56:57.846
This isn't fair.

56:57.848 --> 57:00.582
They just want to get rid of
him because of the bad press.

57:00.584 --> 57:01.850
Well, you know the board.

57:01.852 --> 57:03.485
They're not gonna
take that risk.

57:03.487 --> 57:05.554
Screw the board, Eric.

57:05.556 --> 57:07.756
I know this guy for 10 years.

57:07.758 --> 57:09.491
He's my friend!

57:09.493 --> 57:10.492
What do you want me to do!

57:10.494 --> 57:12.694
I want you to let him go.

57:12.696 --> 57:17.032
No, it's not a fair decision,
but it's the correct one.

57:17.034 --> 57:21.203
And there's too much of
a risk for the company.

57:21.205 --> 57:22.538
You've got to let
him go, sherman.

57:41.192 --> 57:43.225
You don't have to do this.

57:43.227 --> 57:45.461
If you just finish writing
your last book then maybe--

57:45.463 --> 57:46.562
I'm done.

57:46.564 --> 57:47.996
Finished.

57:47.998 --> 57:50.666
I don't care, sherman.

57:50.668 --> 57:52.501
Don't you get it?

57:52.503 --> 57:53.802
I don't wanna write.

57:53.804 --> 57:55.804
I wanna go back and find her.

57:55.806 --> 57:58.707
Blake, it's been five months.

57:58.709 --> 58:00.042
You've got to let her go.

58:00.044 --> 58:02.611
Let the police and-- and
Melbourne do their job.

58:02.613 --> 58:03.579
He isn't doing shit.

58:03.581 --> 58:06.582
They still think I did it.

58:06.584 --> 58:09.585
The divorce left
me almost bankrupt,

58:09.587 --> 58:11.119
but I still got
enough to survive.

58:14.725 --> 58:17.159
I won't stop till i
find her, sherman.

58:17.161 --> 58:18.160
Come on.

58:18.162 --> 58:19.127
I can't.

59:04.875 --> 59:08.977
Listen, you've been
a really good friend.

59:08.979 --> 59:11.146
I'll always be
grateful for that.

59:11.148 --> 59:13.882
Stay in the cabin for
as long as you need.

59:13.884 --> 59:17.586
Melbourne's a good guy,
and you can trust him.

59:17.588 --> 59:18.220
Yeah.

59:29.934 --> 59:30.732
You can hand these out.

59:33.671 --> 59:34.303
You never know.

59:54.258 --> 59:56.825
Come on, girl.

01:00:59.056 --> 01:01:00.355
Melbourne, what's up?

01:01:00.357 --> 01:01:03.759
Listen, I need you
to go see someone.

01:01:30.254 --> 01:01:31.119
Hey, folks.

01:01:31.121 --> 01:01:32.254
How you doin'?

01:01:32.256 --> 01:01:33.355
Here's a picture
of my girlfriend.

01:01:33.357 --> 01:01:35.157
She's been missing for a while.

01:01:35.159 --> 01:01:37.292
I'd like you to keep a copy of
this, ask some of your friends.

01:01:51.909 --> 01:01:52.841
Mr. blackman?

01:01:52.843 --> 01:01:53.442
Yeah.

01:02:04.254 --> 01:02:05.053
May I?

01:02:21.305 --> 01:02:23.772
Straight down the hallway.

01:02:23.774 --> 01:02:24.506
He's waitin' on ya.

01:02:54.805 --> 01:02:56.004
It's ok, buddy.

01:03:00.511 --> 01:03:04.346
And now, do you know why
you're here, Mr. blackman?

01:03:08.252 --> 01:03:10.218
Melbourne told me
to come see you.

01:03:10.220 --> 01:03:12.053
He did, huh?

01:03:12.055 --> 01:03:13.855
What else did he say?

01:03:13.857 --> 01:03:16.458
That it was urgent.

01:03:16.460 --> 01:03:19.027
Urgent.

01:03:19.029 --> 01:03:20.996
Guns.

01:03:20.998 --> 01:03:26.334
How many innocent
people killed by 'em.

01:03:26.336 --> 01:03:29.471
What's happening
in this country?

01:03:29.473 --> 01:03:35.043
Children-- children are
killing other children.

01:03:35.045 --> 01:03:39.080
All these shootings
at schools, god.

01:03:39.082 --> 01:03:40.015
They're just babies.

01:03:42.352 --> 01:03:43.151
It's unbearable.

01:03:46.523 --> 01:03:51.426
And now there's people missing
in my town, Mr. blackman.

01:03:56.400 --> 01:03:57.465
I know who you are.

01:03:57.467 --> 01:03:59.167
Oh, yeah?

01:03:59.169 --> 01:04:00.068
Who?

01:04:00.070 --> 01:04:02.237
You're seagrass lambert.

01:04:02.239 --> 01:04:05.040
You own all the coal
mines in the area.

01:04:05.042 --> 01:04:10.111
First boy that went missing was
your grandson, James lambert

01:04:10.113 --> 01:04:14.082
vanished February 19th about
3:00 pm on his way home

01:04:14.084 --> 01:04:16.318
from school.

01:04:16.320 --> 01:04:18.320
Last person that saw him
was the school bus driver.

01:04:21.291 --> 01:04:22.090
It was a Friday.

01:04:26.396 --> 01:04:31.066
It was a Friday and i
promised him we'd go fishin'.

01:04:31.068 --> 01:04:34.469
My only grandson
has disappeared.

01:04:38.242 --> 01:04:40.542
Gone!

01:04:40.544 --> 01:04:45.480
Gone from the face of the
earth, leaving no trace.

01:04:49.052 --> 01:04:50.318
Why am I here?

01:04:50.320 --> 01:04:52.921
Because the whole
world thinks that you

01:04:52.923 --> 01:04:56.625
had something to do with your
girlfriend's disappearance.

01:04:56.627 --> 01:04:58.326
The police think you did it.

01:04:58.328 --> 01:05:02.597
The entire town thinks you
did it, except for Melbourne.

01:05:02.599 --> 01:05:09.237
And lucky for you-- damn lucky
for you, I like Melbourne.

01:05:10.440 --> 01:05:11.907
I trust him.

01:05:11.909 --> 01:05:15.043
You still haven't
answered my question.

01:05:15.045 --> 01:05:20.515
Melbourne says
that you need this.

01:05:22.252 --> 01:05:26.087
Maybe the cases are connected.

01:05:35.532 --> 01:05:38.233
Is that what this is about?

01:05:38.235 --> 01:05:39.701
Well, Melbourne's wrong.

01:05:39.703 --> 01:05:42.103
I'm not looking for a handout.

01:05:42.105 --> 01:05:44.105
I'll see myself out.

01:05:44.107 --> 01:05:45.540
Bullshit.

01:05:45.542 --> 01:05:48.243
We all know what
you did in New York.

01:05:48.245 --> 01:05:52.047
By the time this is all done,
you'll be so damn broke, you'll

01:05:52.049 --> 01:05:53.949
be begging for money.

01:05:53.951 --> 01:05:56.685
Don't be so proud.

01:05:56.687 --> 01:05:58.053
Take it.

01:05:58.055 --> 01:06:00.588
A gift.

01:06:00.590 --> 01:06:03.224
Police haven't
found anything yet.

01:06:03.226 --> 01:06:06.461
If you trace who did
it, there's a chance you

01:06:06.463 --> 01:06:08.163
might find out who took my boy.

01:06:10.701 --> 01:06:11.533
Hope.

01:06:15.505 --> 01:06:17.038
That's all I got.

01:06:20.177 --> 01:06:20.976
Hope.

01:06:23.680 --> 01:06:24.746
I don't mean to
be disrespectful.

01:06:31.355 --> 01:06:35.490
No photos of your boy?

01:06:35.492 --> 01:06:36.291
No.

01:06:39.029 --> 01:06:39.627
It's so painful.

01:06:43.200 --> 01:06:50.205
I appreciate the gesture,
but, uh, still I'm gonna pass.

01:06:50.207 --> 01:06:52.173
Melbourne was right about you.

01:06:52.175 --> 01:06:55.110
How's that?

01:06:55.112 --> 01:06:58.346
He's been.

01:06:58.348 --> 01:07:04.753
They had what you have--
the will to never give up.

01:07:04.755 --> 01:07:10.492
If you need anything,
people in this town owe me.

01:07:12.562 --> 01:07:13.361
Sir.

01:07:17.300 --> 01:07:20.268
One more thing.

01:07:20.270 --> 01:07:23.671
No one ever asked for ransom.

01:07:23.673 --> 01:07:26.808
They never asked for a dime.

01:07:26.810 --> 01:07:29.511
So the motive can't
be money, can it?

01:08:09.319 --> 01:08:13.688
I wore this when I was
pregnant with twins.

01:08:13.690 --> 01:08:16.624
Oh, there.

01:08:16.626 --> 01:08:18.792
That's better.

01:08:18.795 --> 01:08:22.764
Oh-- oh, I'm sure it's a boy.

01:08:22.765 --> 01:08:26.367
It's just gotta be a boy!

01:08:26.368 --> 01:08:29.571
You are huge!

01:08:29.573 --> 01:08:31.805
Angie.

01:08:31.808 --> 01:08:33.808
Angie.

01:08:33.810 --> 01:08:36.644
I'm not a monster.

01:08:36.645 --> 01:08:43.283
It's just that Leonard, he
don't like the boys running off.

01:08:43.819 --> 01:08:49.424
It's so-- it's so easy for
young boys to get hurt.

01:08:49.426 --> 01:08:52.660
And that's right.

01:08:52.662 --> 01:08:57.432
And we even got bear
traps out there.

01:08:57.434 --> 01:08:59.200
Bear traps?

01:08:59.202 --> 01:09:06.174
Huge bear traps out
there in the woods.

01:09:06.176 --> 01:09:11.145
You understand-- you
understand, Angie, don't you?

01:09:11.148 --> 01:09:12.881
Yeah.

01:09:12.883 --> 01:09:14.415
I understand, Margaret.

01:09:17.720 --> 01:09:18.685
Shh.

01:09:18.688 --> 01:09:19.520
Hush!

01:09:37.573 --> 01:09:39.573
What!

01:09:39.576 --> 01:09:41.576
Nothin'.

01:09:41.578 --> 01:09:43.711
My food ready yet?

01:09:43.712 --> 01:09:45.747
Yes, it is.

01:09:45.749 --> 01:09:48.383
It's on the table,
you blind fool!

01:09:59.296 --> 01:10:00.662
, here.

01:10:06.636 --> 01:10:07.602
Ah!

01:10:07.604 --> 01:10:08.469
Oh.

01:10:08.471 --> 01:10:09.604
A-- Angie?

01:10:09.606 --> 01:10:10.738
Are you ok?
-Yeah.

01:10:10.740 --> 01:10:11.639
Yeah.

01:10:11.641 --> 01:10:12.941
Don't worry about me.

01:10:12.943 --> 01:10:13.975
You guys eat.

01:10:13.977 --> 01:10:15.510
Quick, before she comes down.

01:10:22.886 --> 01:10:26.354
I'm sorry, Mr. blackman,
but we already told you.

01:10:26.356 --> 01:10:29.457
Dr. Morris cannot discuss
his patient's information

01:10:29.459 --> 01:10:30.792
with anyone.

01:10:30.794 --> 01:10:31.993
I understand that, but please--

01:10:31.995 --> 01:10:33.995
we've been through
this, remember?

01:10:33.997 --> 01:10:38.566
You must address your concerns
with the police, not us.

01:10:38.568 --> 01:10:40.835
This is my girlfriend
we're talkin' about.

01:10:40.837 --> 01:10:43.238
She was pregnant with my baby.

01:10:43.240 --> 01:10:44.839
Please, I'm begging you.

01:10:44.841 --> 01:10:46.507
It's been five months and the
police haven't found anything!

01:10:46.509 --> 01:10:50.979
Mr blackman, we can't help you!

01:10:50.981 --> 01:10:53.314
I'm afraid I'm going to
have to ask you to leave.

01:10:56.853 --> 01:10:57.652
Right.

01:11:07.530 --> 01:11:09.797
Yeah.

01:11:09.799 --> 01:11:10.598
I understand.

01:11:13.470 --> 01:11:14.335
Yes, sir.

01:11:14.337 --> 01:11:16.271
We'll do that.

01:11:16.273 --> 01:11:16.871
Bye.

01:11:19.776 --> 01:11:21.676
FBI?

01:11:21.678 --> 01:11:24.012
They're ready to step in.

01:11:24.014 --> 01:11:24.846
Anything?

01:11:24.848 --> 01:11:26.814
Afraid not, sir.

01:11:26.816 --> 01:11:29.751
It's been months and no leads.

01:11:29.753 --> 01:11:32.654
Those boys, Thompson,
what a nightmare.

01:11:32.656 --> 01:11:35.490
Blackman's case ain't
helping us either.

01:11:35.492 --> 01:11:37.058
He's a well-known writer.

01:11:37.060 --> 01:11:38.926
People are digging into it.

01:11:38.928 --> 01:11:41.062
Melbourne still helping him?

01:11:41.064 --> 01:11:43.665
As far as I know, yes.

01:11:43.667 --> 01:11:44.465
That old fox.

01:11:46.970 --> 01:11:48.536
Son of a bitch, he's good.

01:11:48.538 --> 01:11:50.672
You want me to talk to him?

01:11:50.674 --> 01:11:51.773
I can call him.

01:11:51.775 --> 01:11:53.441
Nah, never mind.

01:11:53.443 --> 01:11:58.946
Truth is we've got
nothin' on blackman.

01:11:58.948 --> 01:12:02.817
Phone records indicate that
the victim's 911 call was

01:12:02.819 --> 01:12:04.919
made nowhere near the cabin.

01:12:04.921 --> 01:12:09.023
What about that gas
station kid, Tommy?

01:12:09.025 --> 01:12:15.063
He remembers nothin.' Just
her SUV getting gas that day.

01:12:15.065 --> 01:12:17.365
These cases are gettin'
as cold as the weather.

01:12:38.855 --> 01:12:41.389
Stay here, girl.

01:12:41.391 --> 01:12:42.023
Stay.

01:12:57.440 --> 01:12:58.139
Do you know who I am?

01:12:58.141 --> 01:12:59.741
Listen, dude.

01:12:59.743 --> 01:13:02.143
I already told the police
everything that I know.

01:13:02.145 --> 01:13:03.845
Try harder.

01:13:03.847 --> 01:13:06.714
Are you 100% sure you didn't
see anybody else that day?

01:13:06.716 --> 01:13:07.849
Yeah.

01:13:07.851 --> 01:13:10.785
Nobody in here
inside the store?

01:13:10.787 --> 01:13:12.787
You guys have any
security cameras?

01:13:12.789 --> 01:13:15.490
Security cameras?

01:13:15.492 --> 01:13:16.424
Never mind.

01:13:16.426 --> 01:13:18.626
It's ok.

01:13:18.628 --> 01:13:19.427
Sorry.

01:13:24.067 --> 01:13:27.101
What pump did she use that day?

01:13:27.103 --> 01:13:29.170
Pump one, the same
one that you're at.

01:14:08.044 --> 01:14:09.076
Hey.

01:14:09.078 --> 01:14:11.612
What about the diesel pump area?

01:14:11.614 --> 01:14:12.747
No.

01:14:12.749 --> 01:14:15.116
Anybody fixing
any cars or tires?

01:14:15.118 --> 01:14:17.185
Not-- I don't know.

01:14:21.524 --> 01:14:22.156
Wait.

01:14:22.158 --> 01:14:23.925
Wait.

01:14:23.927 --> 01:14:26.527
I remember seeing a white Chevy.

01:14:26.529 --> 01:14:27.929
Wh-- what kind of Chevy?

01:14:27.931 --> 01:14:31.766
It was an old white impala
with a, um, flat tire.

01:14:31.768 --> 01:14:34.202
But it was way before
your girlfriend came in.

01:14:34.204 --> 01:14:36.737
Are you sure it was an impala?

01:14:36.739 --> 01:14:38.139
Yeah.

01:14:38.141 --> 01:14:40.775
It was old, like from the
'60s, and it was rusty.

01:14:40.777 --> 01:14:42.009
All right.

01:14:42.011 --> 01:14:43.845
Well, did you see
who was driving it?

01:14:43.847 --> 01:14:44.846
No.

01:14:44.848 --> 01:14:46.247
Sure?

01:14:46.249 --> 01:14:49.250
Yeah.

01:14:49.252 --> 01:14:52.053
Well, did you tell the police?

01:14:52.055 --> 01:14:53.654
No.

01:14:53.656 --> 01:14:56.791
So I'm the only one that knows.

01:14:56.793 --> 01:14:58.926
Yeah.

01:14:58.928 --> 01:14:59.727
Thanks.

01:15:32.862 --> 01:15:34.128
Oh!

01:15:34.130 --> 01:15:35.796
May I help you?

01:15:35.798 --> 01:15:40.001
I need to search for vehicles
registered in the '60s.

01:15:40.003 --> 01:15:40.935
Ma'am, please.

01:15:40.937 --> 01:15:42.203
I'm in a hurry.

01:15:42.205 --> 01:15:45.239
Aren't you that fella
that I have seen?

01:15:45.241 --> 01:15:47.208
Yes, I am.

01:15:47.210 --> 01:15:49.677
And who is that?

01:15:49.679 --> 01:15:51.245
That's Brandi.

01:15:51.247 --> 01:15:52.947
Oh.

